tags.description: From 1993 to Sept 2024, the American Mountaineering Center was jointly owned and operated in this building by the American Alpine Club and the Colorado Mountain Club. 1997: listed on National Register of Historic Places: 2024: sold to Coors.
tags.fixme: Building was sold Sept 2024. The CMC has already moved to a new location and the AAC plans to do the same. Update name after Coors renovates the building.
tags.name: American Mountaineering Center
tags.note: The American Mountaineering Museum was part of the American Mountaineering Center. Since the building is on the National Register of Historic Places, it will be renovated by Coors.
